metadata.name: Irune
metadata.description:
Irune was a young girl who lived in a small town in the countryside of Spain. She grew up during the turbulent years of World War II, and like many others her age, was fascinated by the bravery and adventure of the pilots who fought in the skies.

As she grew older, Irune became increasingly determined to join the war effort and serve her country. 

One day, her chance finally came. The Spanish government was looking for brave and skilled pilots to join their airforce, and Irune seized the opportunity to prove herself.

She passed all the rigorous tests and was accepted into the airforce.

In the end, Irune survived the war, and went on to fly for many years afterwards, always striving to inspire others with her passion for flight and her unwavering love of freedom. She remained a beloved hero in the hearts of those who knew her, and her story was passed down from generation to generation as a testament to the strength and courage of the human spirit.
